	<text>
		<body>
			<pb n="1R"/>
				<p rend="align(right)"><placeName>New Orleans</placeName> <date>Sept 29 1862</date></p>
				<p><addressee>Rev Isaac Leeser</addressee></p>
			<p rend="indent(2)">Being unable to<lb/> attend to the packing of your<lb/> Books I find the person so doing has sent you all <sic>He</sic><lb/> found  I think you will find<lb/> some Books of <persName>Isaac<lb/> Wise</persName> and one <sic>sett</sic> of German<lb/> <sic>Preyers</sic> not of your publication<lb/> please return by Express any books not belonging to you so <add>&#63;</add>.</p>
			<p rend="indent(2)">Your old friend  <persName role="author">Isaac Hart</persName></p>
				<p>I feel hurt your not sending me<lb/> the Occident as well as others<lb/> do &#38; I am willing to pay<lb/> for it I am as ever at your service</p>
			<p rend="indent(8)"><persName role="author">T. O.</persName></p>
				<p rend="The following is written in pencil at the bottom center of the page.">E</p>
			<pb n="1V"/>
				<p>The <sic>Pourtigese</sic> Synagogue was<lb/> well attended during <date>Roush<add>&#63;</add> a<lb/> Shona</date>.  <persName>Gutheim</persName> lectured<lb/> the first night &#38; such was his<lb/> eloquence that scarcely a Dry eye<lb/> among either sex.  I attended the<lb/> <add>&#63;</add> Synagogue the first day<lb/> it was not crowded but crammed<lb/> I never saw it so full by both sexes<lb/> <persName>Dr.  Illoway</persName> Lectured both days<lb/> &#38; also <add>Hebrew</add> Shuvar &#40;<date>repentance<lb/> day</date>&#41; the <date>2<hi rend="sup">nd</hi> day Roush a Shona</date><lb/> I attended the Polish Shool<lb/> They have a finely fitted up place<lb/> over the <placeName>Carrolton Rroad</placeName> Depot<lb/>  Their Hazan has a magnificent<lb/> Voice but he did not read<lb/> the <date>2<hi rend="sup">nd</hi> day</date>.  Musaph was read in<lb/> a solemn &#38; beautiful style<lb/> by the Sandac.  I was the<lb/> <sic>receipiant</sic> of many honors<lb/> &#38; kind attentions on the</p>
				<p rend="Vertical blue lines under writing on entire page. The following is written at the bottom of the page&#59;"><date>9&#45;29&#45;1862</date> E</p>
			<pb n="2R"/>
				<p>occasion &#38; was seated next to<lb/> their President <persName>L Kaiser Esq</persName><lb/> Their Cemetery is nearly opposite that<lb/> of the <sic>Pourtugese</sic> &#38; is beautifully<lb/> laid out while speaking of<lb/> Burial Grounds I must mention<lb/> the Rampart Congregation have lately<lb/> erected a massive &#38; beautiful brick<lb/> Wall all round their old cemetery<lb/> on <placeName>Jackson St </placeName>&#38; the District.  <sic>Haveing</sic><lb/> purchased &#38; laid out on family Lots<lb/> a very large piece of Ground at the<lb/> <placeName>junction of Gentilly<add>&#63;</add> Road &#38; the<lb/> Ponchalian R Road</placeName>.  The style<lb/> of everything connected with it is on<lb/> the modern style &#38; a credit to the<lb/> Congregation <persName>Mr Friedlander</persName> is still<lb/> their presiding officer &#38; does all<lb/> in his power to Benefit the<lb/> Congregation notwithstanding<lb/> nor <add>&#63;</add> existing our Congregations<lb/> &#38; Benevolent Societies continue to flourish&#8212;</p>
			<p rend="indent(6)">Yours &#38;c</p>
			<p rend="indent(6)"><persName role="author">I H</persName></p>
		</body>
